title: So consider n = 2.
pid: 2c20b214-0879-47a4-af12-0f536bfe0a78
body: |2-
  In this case FZ : (Fin 2 = Fin (S 1)),
    so k = 1.
  The next element is FS FZ, because
    FS : Fin k -> Fin (S k)
       = Fin 1 -> Fin 2
  The next element cannot exist, because
    FS (FS (FZ : Fin 1) : Fin 2) : Fin 3
